      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Continuum FEA with elastic-plastic material model and nonlinear contact demonstrated to capture relevant physics for metallic implant constructs under quasi-static bending.",
      "rationale": "The ensemble uses continuum FEA with bilinear elastic-plastic material models and nonlinear frictional contact at screw-rod and screw-block interfaces. This model form is well-established for metallic spinal implant constructs under quasi-static loading and is consistent with prior FDA validation studies."
