    "role": "Credibility assessment team",
    "outcome": "Accepted",
    "rationale": "The credibility assessment for COU1 is accepted. Twelve of thirteen V&V 40 credibility factors meet or exceed the required level for Medium model risk. The single deficiency in Test conditions (achieved level 2 vs. required level 3) reflects the standardized single-condition nature of the ASTM F1717 protocol and is mitigated by the high relevance of that condition to clinical use, the multi-laboratory experimental dataset, and the three-code FEA ensemble. All QoI acceptance criteria (<10% difference, E/uval < 1.96) are satisfied. The overall evidence package provides adequate credibility to support the regulatory decision for this Class II device.",
